<h2>Character Design Analysis in Dragonsweeper</h2>
<h3>Protagonist: Jorge</h3>
<p>Jorge serves as the player-controlled protagonist in <em><a href="https://www.dragonsweepers.net/" title="Dragonsweeper">Dragonsweeper</a></em>, portrayed as a courageous adventurer tasked with exploring and eliminating monsters inhabiting the game board. His health points (HP), displayed prominently in the bottom-left corner of the screen, function as a core gameplay mechanic. Notably, Jorge can survive at zero HP without immediate death, granting players strategic flexibility to explore high-risk areas.</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Health Potions</strong>: Found during exploration for HP recovery.</li>
  <li><strong>Upgrades</strong>: Purchased with gold to enhance HP and abilities.</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3>Monster System</h3>
<p>The game features diverse monsters hidden across grid tiles:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Power Values</strong>: Determine attack strength (higher values = greater damage).</li>
  <li><strong>Special Traits</strong>: Unique abilities or distribution patterns requiring player observation.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Example Monsters</h4>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Demon</strong>: High-power early-game enemy.</li>
  <li><strong>Slime</strong>: Low-power but appears in swarms.</li>
  <li><strong>Bat</strong>: Weak but unpredictably distributed.</li>
</ul>

<p>A <strong>Bestiary</strong> catalogs encountered monsters for strategic analysis.</p>
<img src="/t-p.png" title="Dragonsweeper Official Monster System">
<br>
<h3>Interface & Auxiliary Elements</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>HP Display</strong>: Real-time health tracking.</li>
  <li><strong>Health Potions</strong>: Instant HP recovery.</li>
  <li><strong>Gold & Upgrades</strong>: Currency for permanent stat boosts.</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3>Strategy & Gameplay</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Plan Routes</strong>: Balance exploration with risk mitigation.</li>
  <li><strong>HP as Resource</strong>: Trade health for information/gold.</li>
  <li><strong>Analyze Monsters</strong>: Adapt tactics based on enemy traits.</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3>Conclusion</h3>
<p><em>Dragonsweeper</em> merges traditional Minesweeper mechanics with RPG progression through its character and monster designs.</p>
